# Customer Churn Prediction using Logistic Regression

## Overview

This project predicts customer churn using Logistic Regression on a real telecom dataset.

The objective is to identify customers likely to leave the company and generate actionable business insights.

---

## Dataset

Telco Customer Churn Dataset

* 7,032 customers
* 30 engineered features after preprocessing

---

## Project Workflow

1. Data Cleaning
2. Handling Missing Values
3. Encoding Categorical Variables
4. Train/Test Split
5. Feature Scaling
6. Logistic Regression Modeling
7. Performance Evaluation
8. Business Insights Extraction

---

## Model Performance

| Metric    | Score |
| --------- | ----- |
| Accuracy  | 80.4% |
| Precision | 64.8% |
| Recall    | 57.5% |
| F1 Score  | 60.9% |

---

## Key Business Insights

* Customers with month-to-month contracts show higher churn risk.
* Long-term contracts strongly reduce churn.
* Fiber optic customers show elevated churn probability.
* New customers are more likely to leave.

---

